text: The TCP/IP processing agent allows data to be distributed from a workflow, using the standard TCP/IP protocol. Several connections at a time are allowed. The agent can also send various UDRs back into the workflow. All handling of these UDRs are done through APL commands. Warning! Deprecation Netty version 3 is deprecated from version 9.0.0 of MediationZone. The TCP/IP forwarding agent supports IPv4 and IPv6 environments. Open A TCP/IP forwarding workflow example The section contains the following subsections: TCP/IP Processing UDR Types TCP/IP Processing Agent Configuration TCP/IP Processing Agent Input/Output Data and MIM TCP/IP Processing Agent Events
